'''Anaqua''' is a [[Boston]],  [[Massachusetts|MA]] based provider of intellectual asset management (IAM) and [[Software as a service|SaaS]] software and services.<ref name=venture>{{cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2013/10/17/anaqua-secures-25m-from-bessemer-to-protect-your-ip/|title=Anaqua secures $25M to guard your trademarks, patents, and other valuable creations|publisher=Venture Beat|accessdate=November 16, 2013}}</ref><ref name=chicago>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagogrid.com/reviews/tech/iit-intellectual-property-degree/|title=A New Economy Means A New Kind Of Theft — And A New IIT Degree To Prevent It|publisher=Chicago Grid|accessdate=November 16, 2013}}</ref><ref name="Finsmes.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.finsmes.com/2013/07/anaqua-receives-significant-investment-insight-venture-partners.html |title=Anaqua Receives Significant Investment From Insight Venture Partners |accessdate=2013-09-27 |date=2013-07-17}}</ref><ref name="Pulse2.com">{{cite web |url=http://pulse2.com/2013/07/17/anaqua-raises-100-million-to-store-your-i-p-in-the-cloud-89898/ |accessdate=2013-09-27 |title=Anaqua Raises $100 Million to Store Your I.P. in the Cloud |publisher=Pulse 2.0}}</ref><ref name="Ipwatchdog.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.ipwatchdog.com/2012/05/07/5-things-to-know-about-patent-law-firm-management/id=24227/ |title=5Things to Know About Patent Law Firm Management |year=2013 |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref> Anaqua’s Enterprise IAM solution supports the full IA lifecycle{{lopsided|date=September 2014}} from idea to monetization for all IA categories, including inventions, patents, trade secrets, brands and trademarks.<ref name="Allthingsd.com">{{cite web |url=http://allthingsd.com/20130717/anaqua-ip-management-in-the-cloud-lands-100-million-from-insight/ |author=Arik Hesseldahl |date=2013-07-17 |publisher=All Things D |title=Anaqua, IP Management in the Cloud Lands $100 Million From Insight |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref><ref name="Ipfrontline.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.ipfrontline.com/depts/article.aspx?id=14260&deptid=8 |title=IP, Veteran, Ralph Schroeder, Joins Anaqua Management Team |date=2007-02-15}}</ref><ref name="Valuewalk.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.valuewalk.com/2013/07/beacon-equity-sells-anaqua-insight-venture/ |title=Beacon Equity Sells Anaqua to Insight Venture |author=Marie Cabural |publisher=Value Walk |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref><ref name="Techsling.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.techsling.com/2013/08/intellectual-asset-management-solutions/ |title=Intellectual Asset Management Solutions |date=2013-08-09 |accessdate=2013-09-27 |publisher=TechSling}}</ref><ref name="Maschoffbrennan.com">{{cite web |url=http://maschoffbrennan.com/mgi-deploys-anaqua-essential/ |title=MGI Deploys Anaqua Essential |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref> Anaqua Express is designed for smaller IP teams.<ref name="Techsling.com"/><ref name="Maschoffbrennan.com"/> Anaqua Element is a quick start,{{lopsided|date=September 2014}} cloud-based solution for IP professionals managing small portfolios.<ref name="Allthingsd.com"/><ref name="Techsling.com"/> Anaqua Essential helps law firms manage intellectual assets on behalf of clients.<ref name="Maschoffbrennan.com"/><ref name=bessemer>{{cite web|url=http://www.bvp.com/blog/bvp-invests-anaqua-fund-future-ip-management|title=BVP invests in Anaqua to fund the future of IP management|publisher=Bessemer Venture Partners|accessdate=November 16, 2013}}</ref><ref name=boston>{{cite web|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/boston/blog/startups/2013/10/ip-software-firm-anaqua-raises-25m.html|title=IP software firm Anaqua raises $25M from Bessemer|publisher=Boston Business Journal|accessdate=November 16, 2013}}</ref>

==History==

Anaqua was formed in 2004 and bought by Beacon Equity Partners in 2005.<ref name="Ivcpost.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.ivcpost.com/articles/11711/20130722/anaqua-sold-insight-venture-partners.htm |title=Anaqua sold off to Insight Venture Partners |date=2013-07-22 |accessdate=2013-09-27 |publisher=Venture Capital Post}}</ref>
In 2006, Anaqua received $4 million from Northstar Global Partners, which they used to relocate headquarters from [[London]] to [[Boston]] and hire more staff.<ref name="Allthingsd.com"/><ref name="Bizjournals.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/boston/stories/2006/02/20/story8.html?page=all |author= Lisa va der Pool |title=Software maker Anaqua arrives in Hub with$4M|date=2006-02-20 |publisher=Boston Business Journal |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref>  In 2010 Anaqua merged with SGA2, an ISO 9000-certified supplier of global patent annuity and trademark renewal services.<ref name="Maschoffbrennan.com"/><ref name="Iam-magazine.com">{{cite web |title=Anaqua|url=http://www.iam-magazine.com/partners/Default.aspx |publisher=Intellectual Asset Management |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref>  In 2013, Beacon Equity Partners sold Anaqua to Insight Venture Partners.<ref name="Finsmes.com"/><ref name="Pulse2.com"/><ref name="Allthingsd.com"/><ref name="Ivcpost.com"/><ref name="Dowjones.com">{{cite web |url=http://pevc.dowjones.com/Article?an=DJFVW00020130717e97hp23q2&cid=32135016&ctype=ts&pid=32&ReturnUrl=http%3a%2f%2fpevc.dowjones.com%2fArticle%3fan%3dDJFVW00020130717e97hp23q2%26cid%3d32135016%26ctype%3dts%26pid%3d32 |title=Anaqua Lands $100M From Insight Venture Partners |author=Jonathan Shieber |date=2013-07-17 |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref>

Priya Iyer joined Anaqua as the chief operating officer in 2005 and was promoted to CEO in 2007.<ref name="Mit.edu">{{cite web |url=http://mitsloan.mit.edu/fellows/fellows-present-past/alumni-network/ |publisher=MIT Sloan Management |title=Meet alumni |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref><ref name="Technologyreview.com">{{cite web |url=http://www2.technologyreview.com/Emtech/archive/08/speakers.aspx |title=EmTech08 Speakers |publisher=Technology Review |year=2008 |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref><ref name="Businessweek.com">{{cite web |url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=26145752&privcapId=26015633 |title=Priya Iyer |publisher=Bloomberg Businessweek |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref> Bob Romeo took over as CEO in August 2015.{{cn|date=September 2018}}

Anaqua merged with Lecorpio, LLC, announced on July 25, 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.anaqua.com/company/news/anaqua-and-lecorpio-merge-create-next-generation-ip-software-and-services-company|title=Anaqua and Lecorpio Merge to Create Next Generation IP Software and Services Company|last=Anaqua|date=2017-07-21|work=Anaqua|access-date=2017-07-28|language=en}}</ref>

